plt.plot(t, np.sin(t))

$ f(t) = A \cos(2 \pi f t + \phi)$

$ f(t) = A \cos(\frac{2 \pi t}{T} + \phi)$

  • A = amplitude
  • f = frequency (in hz, or cycles per second)
  • T = period = 1/f (the length of each repetition, in seconds)
  • t = time
  • $\phi$ = the phase
In [3]:
A = 1
f = 3
t = np.linspace(0, 5, 1000)
phi = np.pi/3
y = A*np.cos(2*np.pi*f*t + phi)
plt.plot(t, y)
plt.ylim([-5, 5])

$f = 440 * 2^{p/12}$¶

In [7]:
def get_note_freq(p):
    return 440*2**(p/12)
In [8]:
t = np.arange(int(sr/2))/sr
f = get_note_freq(0)
y = np.array([])
for p in range(12):
    f = get_note_freq(p)
    y = np.concatenate((y, np.cos(2*np.pi*f*t)))
ipd.Audio(y, rate=sr)
